{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"707ede0a-5c1d-4dc5-8528-8f0a808d99b1","content":"There are two reliable approaches — one project-based, one from raw SDK manifests:\n\n## 1. From an existing MAUI project (easiest)\n\nMSBuild exposes the exact values the SDK expects:\n\n```bash\ndotnet msbuild YourApp.csproj -getProperty:AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion\ndotnet msbuild YourApp.csproj -getProperty:TargetPlatformVersion\ndotnet msbuild YourApp.csproj -getProperty:AndroidCommandLineToolsVersion\n```\n\nThese resolve from the installed workload packs — no guessing.\n\n## 2. From the SDK manifests directly (no project needed)\n\nThis is ideal for CI bootstrap scripts:\n\n```bash\n# Step 1: Find your SDK root\nSDK_ROOT=$(dotnet --list-sdks | tail -1 | sed 's/.* \\[\\(.*\\)\\]/\\1/')\n\n# Step 2: Read the workload manifest to get the Android pack version\ncat \"$SDK_ROOT/../sdk-manifests/\"*/microsoft.net.sdk.android/WorkloadManifest.json\n# → Shows the Microsoft.Android.Sdk pack version (e.g. \"34.0.143\")\n\n# Step 3: Inspect the pack's MSBuild props for the actual requirements\nPACK_DIR=$(ls -d \"$SDK_ROOT/../packs/Microsoft.Android.Sdk.\"*/*/ | head -1)\ngrep -E 'AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion|AndroidCommandLineToolsVersion|TargetPlatformVersion' \\\n  \"$PACK_DIR/tools/\"*.props \"$PACK_DIR/tools/\"*.targets\n```\n\nThis gives you lines like:\n\n```xml\n<AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion>34.0.0</AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion>\n<AndroidCommandLineToolsVersion>11.0</AndroidCommandLineToolsVersion>\n<!-- TargetPlatformVersion maps to the API level (e.g. 34 → android-34) -->\n```\n\n## Translating to `sdkmanager` packages\n\nOnce you have the values, map them to `sdkmanager` package strings:\n\n```bash\nsdkmanager \\\n  \"build-tools;${AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion}\" \\\n  \"platforms;android-${TargetPlatformVersion}\" \\\n  \"cmdline-tools;${AndroidCommandLineToolsVersion}\" \\\n  \"platform-tools\"\n```\n\n**Why this works:** The workload packs shipped with your exact SDK version are the authoritative source for these values — they're the same props MSBuild reads at build time.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0295ac9-71c9-411f-a765-96355ff99ec8","outputTokens":618,"requestId":"F409:1497BC:1F20757:22FF6DB:69E81BB8"},"id":"64428d46-421e-40a8-9dfb-d537dbe14504","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:52:20.803Z","parentId":"f91cb6c7-bf85-4957-a5f7-1984e25752ad"}
